That's interesting. Here's why I said otherwise. Seems to be limited to vals.
```scala
object NotTheRepl {
  def f = {
    class A
    scala.reflect.runtime.currentMirror.classSymbol((new A).getClass)
  }
}
object RunMe extends App {
  println(NotTheRepl.f)
}

// % rcscala RunMe
// class A$1
// %
```
